(225, 2, 11, 0, 0, 1, 2, 0, 'SilverStripe\\Lessons\\AboutPage', '2021-01-05 07:27:02', '2020-12-29 17:00:51', NULL, 'Inherit', 'Inherit', 'about-me', 'About Me', NULL, '<p>I am a consultant gastroenterologist (specialist of the tube from your mouth to your bottom) and internal medicine physician working in public at North Shore and Waitakere Hospital, and in private at Waitemata Endoscopy and Waitemata Specialists.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Medicine</strong></p><p>I grew up in Whangarei, before attending boarding school in Auckland and then studying medicine at Auckland University.</p><p>I started work as a doctor in 2012, and have practiced in Whangarei, Auckland City Hospital including at the New Zealand Liver Transplant Unit, Middlemore and Tauranga Hospitals, and am currently also working in North Shore and Waitakere Hospital.</p><p><strong>Patient goals</strong></p><p>I believe in a compassionate, holistic and comprehensive assessment of the whole patient. I believe in striving for excellence and providing the very best healthcare. I hold myself to a very high standard and keep up to date with the latest in medical innovation, endoscopic techniques and research. My goal is for patients to feel comfortable to share their concerns, then work together to safely and efficiently diagnose and sort these problems.&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 3, 0, 0, NULL, 0),
