hat have been studied that can decrease risk include&nbsp;<span><strong>lifestyle risk factors.</strong></span></p><ul><li>A diet high in fat and red or processed meat and low in fibre</li>\n<li>A sedentary lifestyle</li>\n<li>Cigarette smoking</li>\n<li>Alcohol use – heavy use thought to have a very large impact: increase risk of 44% compared with non-drinkers and occasional drinkers</li>\n<li>Obesity&nbsp;</li>\n</ul><p>Modifying these risk factors may help lower your risk of colorectal cancer, in addition to improving your overall health</p><p><a href="[sitetree_link,id=18]">For more information</a></p>', NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 4, 0, 0, NULL, 0),
